        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Leith Hill Place | Dorking</placeName>
                    <date>August 8<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>I regret extremely that I left home yesterday before the arrival of your note (which was forwarded to me here) &amp; that I do not return home for 3 weeks.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
                    <p> On some future occasion, I hope to have the pleasure of seeing you at Down,<ref target="#foot.f3"/> &amp; with all good wishes &amp; much respect, I remain | My dear Sir, Yours very faithfully | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 Leith … Dorking] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘<hi rend="italic">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S. E. R.</hi>’ </note>
            </div>
            
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the address (see n. 2, below).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">The Darwins visited family in Surrey and Staffordshire between 7 and 22 August 1878 (CD’s ‘Journal’ (Appendix II)).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">In the event, De Vries visited CD on 14 August 1878, while CD was staying at Abinger, Surrey (<ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1218.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Emma Darwin’s</ref> diary (DAR 242)).</note>
        </div>  
      
